# ⚡ Prepaid Commercial Power Consumption System Using Coin Box

A smart embedded system that activates electrical power when coins are inserted and cuts it off when credit is exhausted. Ideal for small shops, dorms, or public kiosks.

## 🔍 Overview
Users insert coins into a connected module that enables power for a limited time based on the amount inserted. A basic automation and metering solution.

## 💡 Features
- Accepts physical coins to activate electrical power
- Displays power credits on an LCD
- Automatically turns off power once credit ends

## 🧰 Tools & Technologies
- **Python**
- **Arduino**
- Coin acceptor module
- LCD screen and relay circuit

## 📘 What I Learned
- Embedded systems with Arduino and sensors
- Coin detection logic and UI with LCD
- Energy management and automation basics

> Built to demonstrate energy saving solutions and prepaid metering systems.
